<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="849" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d849">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Russian Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I beg to inform you
                            that the Secretary of the Navy had advised me that on the 26th instant
                            he received a telegram from the commandant of the navy-yard at Mare
                            Island, Cal., in which he stated that the <hi rend="italic">Lena</hi>
                            left the yard for San Francisco on that date, and would sail thence on
                            Sunday, October 29.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>